The course provides insights into global trends and analyzes their impact on community development through practical examples. The course will improve systematic thinking, will help you see both the reciprocal effects of different levels (macro-meso-micro) in community development as well as how different disciplines complement each other, in order to be able to relate to different processes.
The interdisciplinary course is taught alongside human geographers and economists. The purpose of such cooperation is to model the intricacies of a complex society and to intertwine different scientific disciplines in order to understand modern society as well as the potential of interdisciplinary research in community development.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to provide insight into global processes and the impact those processes have on the sustainable development of communities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student will: - know and understand major global development trends and goals; - understand the theoretical and practical origins of eco-social change; - see how processes at the community level are linked to global development trends; - know and understand the reciprocal effects of social processes at different levels.
